                        { title: "2.6 Integrated Marketing Communications (IMC) & Campaign Management", content: `

                            <p>**Integrated Marketing Communications (IMC)** is a strategic approach that ensures all marketing and promotional tools are cohesively used to deliver a consistent, clear, and compelling brand message. For both fashion/luxury and food, inconsistency can be detrimental, impacting brand perception and consumer trust.</p>

                            <p><strong>Ensuring Consistent Messaging:</strong> The core of IMC is ensuring that every customer touchpoint—whether it's a physical boutique, a digital ad, an email, a social media post, product packaging, or a celebrity endorsement—conveys the same brand story, aesthetic, values, and tone of voice. This creates a unified and immersive brand world for the consumer, building stronger brand recognition and trust.</p>

                            <p><strong>Developing and Executing Marketing Campaigns:</strong> For both industries, campaigns are often complex, multi-channel endeavors requiring meticulous planning and coordination.</p>

                            <ul class="list-disc ml-6">

                                <li>**Fashion/Luxury Campaigns:** Often highly event-driven, centered around new collection launches, fashion weeks, or major brand anniversaries. These involve a complex orchestration of multiple channels:

                                    <ul>

                                        <li>An elaborate **runway show** (physical and/or digital livestreamed globally).</li>

                                        <li>A global **advertising campaign** across print (magazines), digital (programmatic ads, social media), and out-of-home (billboards in fashion capitals).</li>

                                        <li>Exclusive **influencer collaborations** and celebrity ambassadorships coordinated for simultaneous content release.</li>

                                        <li>Dedicated **microsites** or virtual showrooms offering immersive digital experiences.</li>

                                        <li>In-store events, window displays, and visual merchandising aligned with the campaign theme.</li>

                                        <li>Public Relations (PR) efforts to secure media coverage and editorial features.</li>

                                    </ul>

                                </li>

                                <li>**Food Industry Campaigns:** Can center around seasonal promotions (e.g., holiday flavors), new product launches, health trend alignments (e.g., plant-based month), or value propositions (e.g., family-sized packs). Tactics might include:

                                    <ul>

                                        <li>**TV and digital ads** highlighting taste, health benefits, or convenience.</li>

